    "creation_date" : 1343678056,
    "answer_id" : 11728624,
    "question_id" : 4819635,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you prefer immutable data objects, or if you just dont want to be destructive to the input list, you can use Guava's predicates.</p>\n\n<pre><code>ImmutableList.copyOf(Iterables.filter(tourists, Predicates.notNull()))\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 62229,
      "reputation" : 21979,
      "user_id" : 185022,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 81,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/045d1e450716084b2a072b57f37a58c4?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
