    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>list.removeAll(Collections.singleton(null));\n</code></pre>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>It will Throws <strong>UnsupportedException</strong> if you use it on Arrays.asList because it give you <strong>Immutable</strong> copy so it can not be modified. See below the code. It creates <strong>Mutable</strong> copy and will not throw any exception.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<pre><code>public static String[] clean(final String[] v) {\n    List&lt;String&gt; list = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;(Arrays.asList(v));\n    list.removeAll(Collections.singleton(null));\n    return list.toArray(new String[list.size()]);\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4039720,
      "reputation" : 31,
      "user_id" : 3322947,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c20abee2a26bbc2860de47e20a45bc98?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Jobin_vibes",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3322947/jobin-vibes"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1392721716,
    "creation_date" : 1392721716,
    "answer_id" : 21851910,
    "question_id" : 4819635,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This is easy way to remove default null values from arraylist</p>\n\n<pre><code>     tourists.removeAll(Arrays.asList(null));  \n</code></pre>\n\n<p>otherwise String value \"null\" remove from arraylist</p>\n\n<pre><code>       tourists.removeAll(Arrays.asList(\"null\"));  \n</code></pre>\n"
