  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4819635/how-to-efficiently-remove-all-null-elements-from-a-arraylist-or-string-array",
  "title" : "How to efficiently remove all null elements from a ArrayList or String Array?",
  "body" : "<p>I try with a loop like that</p>\n<pre><code>// ArrayList tourists\n\nfor (Tourist t : tourists) {\n    if (t != null) {     \n        t.setId(idForm); \n    }   \n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>But it isn't nice. Can anyone suggest me a better solution?</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Some useful benchmarks to make better decision:</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.mkyong.com/java/while-loop-for-loop-and-iterator-performance-test-java/\" rel=\"noreferrer\">While loop, For loop and Iterator Performance Test</a></p>\n"
}